focus-move-collapsed-to-noncollapsed-ref.html", "editor/reftests/caret-focus-move-collapsed-to-noncollapsed.html", "editor/reftests/reftest.list", "layout/base/nsCaret.cpp", "layout/base/nsCaret.h"], "git_node": "0be31837616678a000dac9d99caecffe1ff92250", "git_parents": ["917a8794b25015becf22861a54ca3f139df23f74"], "node": "a5d457f1e56f4dad2dfc9527d6c6c972ffdbfa6d", "parents": ["74c385294569cd3a0fe6ff1684f43bdca286b751"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2009608 - Don't assign non-live hash table entry r=glandium a=dmeehan\n\nThe problem here is that we use move assignment on a hash table entry that is\nnot live. Although all entries are constructed by HashTable::createTable, they\nmay subsequently be destroyed by HashTableEntry::destroyStoredT(). Therefore it\nis not safe to call any methods on a non live entry.\n\nThis causes a problem for GC barrier wrappers which assume that the object\nstate is valid (and presumably anything that does more than just write the\nassigned data into memory).\n\nThe fix is to construct a new entry in place.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D278629\n", "files": ["mfbt/HashTable.h"], "git_node": "5348f5242579e8b027e9251c331d5fd69a5b7d82", "git_parents": ["0be31837616678a000dac9d99caecffe1ff92250"], "node": "27f67596df104265dec42ae133797a8875da0a80", "parents": ["a5d457f1e56f4dad2dfc9527d6c6c972ffdbfa6d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1768941478, "git_changesets": ["0be31837616678a000dac9d99caecffe1ff92250", "5348f5242579e8b027e9251c331d5fd69a5b7d82"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24398": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tim Xia \u003ctxia@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010108: Add AIFeature base class for GenAI components,  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nIntroduces common interface (id, enable, disable, isEnabled) for AI features.\n\n- Add toolkit/components/ml/AIFeature.sys.mjs\n- Update AIFeature interface enable() and disable() to be async\n- Changed `static id()` to `static get id()` - now accessed as `AIFeature.id` instead of `AIFeature.id()`\n- Changed `static isEnabled()` to `static get isEnabled()` - now accessed as `AIFeature.isEnabled` instead of `AIFeature.isEnabled()`\n- move it to jar.mn\n- add isAllowed\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D278859\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279766\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ml/AIFeature.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ml/jar.mn"], "git_node": "f5fdabef64f1d257681b1c511d66aa9f97913bf0", "git_parents": ["5348f5242579e8b027e9251c331d5fd69a5b7d82"], "node": "70fbdd278b1255852e1fdc746aee7f91766f3ed5", "parents": ["27f67596df104265dec42ae133797a8875da0a80"], "tags": []}], "date": 1768953872, "git_changesets": ["f5fdabef64f1d257681b1c511d66aa9f97913bf0"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24399": {"changesets": [{"author": "John M. Schanck \u003cjschanck@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010919 - reject unsupported webauthn mediation requirements.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279361\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279768\n", "files": ["dom/credentialmanagement/CredentialsContainer.cpp", "dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_get_assertion.html", "dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_make_credential.html", "dom/webidl/CredentialManagement.webidl"], "git_node": "2ed86cf7f1c7ad579e7412bddad59df6fc005f44", "git_parents": ["f5fdabef64f1d257681b1c511d66aa9f97913bf0"], "node": "cc04c71c049f0dddb5a011f0dd7378465b48c87f", "parents": ["70fbdd278b1255852e1fdc746aee7f91766f3ed5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1768953924, "git_changesets": ["2ed86cf7f1c7ad579e7412bddad59df6fc005f44"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24400": {"changesets": [{"author": "James Teow \u003cjteow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1959008 - Add null check for PlacesSemanticHistoryManager and