ps://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279873\n", "files": ["uriloader/base/nsURILoader.cpp"], "git_node": "d612ecffb79d3dc150496df98df6cb45ca9908a3", "git_parents": ["edef27ac117aac2e217923659c7703e50252579d"], "node": "6ffc0bfed02cc9c75a13b74e005b6bd46f6efe9e", "parents": ["0634ee7ed2c3b8b5d0e4c241eced9dcb8c11a093"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769022146, "git_changesets": ["d612ecffb79d3dc150496df98df6cb45ca9908a3"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24411": {"changesets": [{"author": "scottdowne \u003csdowne@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2011247 - Newtab fixing holes in spoc data earlier and for all cases.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279699\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279889\n", "files": ["browser/extensions/newtab/lib/TopSitesFeed.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "535ff03ae450d9768346aaf48bbe60f7faf1c49d", "git_parents": ["d612ecffb79d3dc150496df98df6cb45ca9908a3"], "node": "3691cc55c255e6673878ad9b3f3059911757cc3b", "parents": ["6ffc0bfed02cc9c75a13b74e005b6bd46f6efe9e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769022259, "git_changesets": ["535ff03ae450d9768346aaf48bbe60f7faf1c49d"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24412": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010933. Do better error checking for AVIFDecoderStream.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279454\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279807\n", "files": ["image/decoders/nsAVIFDecoder.cpp"], "git_node": "6f215ca85fcc0d06ca2b4a564066e8c160663404", "git_parents": ["535ff03ae450d9768346aaf48bbe60f7faf1c49d"], "node": "07a3c53eece101bef2f7a2507bb7b856b1f091c5", "parents": ["3691cc55c255e6673878ad9b3f3059911757cc3b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769022319, "git_changesets": ["6f215ca85fcc0d06ca2b4a564066e8c160663404"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24413": {"changesets": [{"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010943: Support reading int64 from int32 stack slot  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279595\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279913\n", "files": ["js/src/jit/JitFrames.cpp", "js/src/jit/Snapshots.cpp", "js/src/jit/Snapshots.h", "js/src/jit/shared/CodeGenerator-shared.cpp", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testJitRValueAlloc.cpp"], "git_node": "1b2c2b7a38adb417e967aff4a2f5a826be98b571", "git_parents": ["6f215ca85fcc0d06ca2b4a564066e8c160663404"], "node": "a54fb634850e3cc6848cb08414d537ad5eab940e", "parents": ["07a3c53eece101bef2f7a2507bb7b856b1f091c5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769022414, "git_changesets": ["1b2c2b7a38adb417e967aff4a2f5a826be98b571"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24414": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2011300 - Handle rdonly-inside-deny policies in FixRecursivePermissions(). r=gcp,jld, a=dmeehan\n\nEffectively, break the inheritance chain at FORCE_DENY boundaries, which\nwas already done when the leaf had FORCE_DENY.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279572\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBroker.cpp"], "git_node": "6393f83c951c41a8466657abac2296cd933692b8", "git_parents": ["1b2c2b7a38adb417e967aff4a2f5a826be98b571"], "node": "ed28fc9159c24df4bcddcf407817879e8e0fd83c", "parents": ["a54fb634850e3cc6848cb08414d537ad5eab940e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2011300 - Remove all DENY rules for file process / sandbox level \u003c= 2. r=jld, a=dmeehan\n\nRight now (even without the other patch) accessing `~/.config/mozilla`\ndoesn't work even from the file:// process, because the DENY rule takes\nprecedence over the rdonly rule that we add here.\n\nBug 2011328 would've caught this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279601\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBroker.cpp", "security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBroker.h", "security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerPolicyFactory.cpp"], "git_node": "48c3d8ca2c889b2e22fead084cad43245423ebd0", "git_parents": ["6393f83c951c41a8466657abac2296cd933692b8"], "node": "8e19ec4661b4db994e891a803d2870f8b0fc5ce0", "parents": ["ed28fc9159c24df4bcddcf407817879e8e0fd83c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2003109 - Improve textarea hard-wrapping further. r=hsivonen a=dmeehan\n\nTurns out there were still various issues:\n\n * There's this \"bonus width\" thing which might make us actually not\n   hard-wrap. Add an option to ignore it.\n\n * Even though \\n does create a breaking opportunity, we don't\n   force-break. Do deal with each line at a time instead.\n\nIt's technically a bit more inefficient (two passes over the string),\nbut seems fine and it's simpler / easier to prove correct.\n\nAdd a few extra tests too.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279394\n", "files": ["dom/serializers/nsPlainTextSerializer.cpp", "dom/serializers/nsPlainTextSerializer.h", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/forms/the-textarea-element/wrapping-transformation.window.js"], "git_node": "f24ac8b0310c554cd905b889324f883f0f9f7a93", "git_parents": ["48c3d8ca2c889b2e22fead084cad43245423ebd0"], "node": "90e149ee7863e69ed001f93d1108d360537cb6c3", "parents": ["8e19ec4661b4db994e891a803d2870f8b0fc5ce0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769024215, "git_changesets": ["6393f83c951c41a8466657abac2296cd933692b8", "48c3d8ca2c889b2e22fead084cad43245423ebd0", "f24ac8b0310c554cd905b889324f883f0f9f7a93"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24415": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010601 - Add a crashtest. r=layout-reviewers,dshin a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nSeems better to test with both a PDF and another random object.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279299\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/css/printing/fixed-pos-object-pdf-crash-print.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/loading/early-hints/resources/example.pdf", "testing/web-platform/tests/loading/early-hints/resources/pdf-with-early-hints.h2.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/resources/example.pdf"], "git_node": "19143efc2fb76b3987d8691b37fdb5187ef4a657", "git_parents": ["f24ac8b0310c554cd905b889324f883f0f9f7a93"], "node": "d096a90ea6b588c4ad72ea4f6a592f4e7cd845de", "parents": ["90e149ee7863e69ed001f93d1108d360537cb6c3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769025735, "git_changesets": ["19143efc2fb76b3987d8691b37fdb5187ef4a657"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "24416": {"changesets": [{"author": "mailelucks \u003cmaile.lucks@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2011219 - Target correct object for browser transparency attribute -  DONTBUILD  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279737\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279898\n", "files": ["browser/components/tabbrowser/content/tabbrowser.js"], "git_node": "4964c160802e204f3e7db600aab2dd41679c3615", "git_parents": ["19143efc2fb76b3987d8691b37fdb5187ef4a657"], "node": "9676ae7e38590a13fae5e555832a497693fea020", "parents": ["d096a90ea6b588c4ad72ea4f6a592f4e7cd845de"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769026897, "git_changesets": ["4964c160802e204f3e7db600aab2dd41679c3615"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24417": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1981883 - Add null check for mBgParent,  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nHttpChannelParent::OnBackgroundParentDestroyed can be called before mIPCClosed is set in ActorDestroy, so mIPCClosed alone cannot be used\nto determine whether the background channel is still open.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279648\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279887\n", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParent.cpp"], "git_node": "b03e4e66ce6c5a76849d318868a9786a34da13da", "git_parents": ["4964c160802e204f3e7db600aab2dd41679c3615"], "node": "90741a02589c0efeb6de80ec26fc9280b033876d", "parents": ["9676ae7e38590a13fae5e555832a497693fea020"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769026937, "git_changesets": ["b03e4e66ce6c5a76849d318868a9786a34da13da"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24418": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dana Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010648 - disable QWACs processing by default for now  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279208\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279918\n", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser_identityPopup_qwacs.js", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml", "security/manager/ssl/QWACs.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "b02e75f44508a21d72ee73a2a3807d85f417bdc0", "git_parents": ["b03e4e66ce6c5a76849d318868a9786a34da13da"], "node": "fc984ba94f776fe5751fd22e5c0bcbea88878d0e", "parents": ["90741a02589c0efeb6de80ec26fc9280b033876d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769026999, "git_changesets": ["b02e75f44508a21d72ee73a2a3807d85f417bdc0"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24419": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003caryx.github@gmx-topmail.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010145 - renew test certificates for 2026.  a=dmeehan\n\nCertificates expire on 2027-02-04.\n\nExtended with the instructions in security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/test_cert_expiration_canary.js\n\nIf this test and only this test fails, do the following:\n1. Create a bug for the issue in \"Core :: Security: PSM\".\n2. Write a patch to temporarily disable the test.\n3. Land the patch.\n4. Write a patch to reenable the test but don't land it.\n5. Needinfo the triage owner of Bugzilla's \"Core :: Security: PSM\" component\n   in the bug.\n6. Patches to update certificates get created.\n6.1. Update certificates in security/manager/ssl/tests/unit with\n     ./mach generate-test-certs\n6.2. Update more certificates with\n     ./mach python build/pgo/genpgocert.py\n6.3. Temporarily uncomment the code in security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/test_signed_apps/moz.build,\n     build Firefox with |./mach build| and copy the relevant non-build files\n     from the related object directory folder into this folder.\n6.4. Update the certificate fingerprints mentioned in\n     security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/test_cert_override_read.js with\n     openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/bad_certs/certName.pem\n6.5. Update the base64 encoded serial numbers of test-int.pem and other-test-ca.pem in\n     security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/test_cert_storage.js\n6.5.1. Get the serial number value\n       openssl x509 -noout -in security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/bad_certs/test-int.pem -serial\n6.5.2. base64 encode the hex value without the prefix\n6.5.3. Update base64 encoded value in the test file.\n7. Commit the changes: Mention the year of the update, the date of the\n   next expiration and add these instructions to the commit message.\n8. Test the patches with a Try push.\n9. Land the patches on all trees whose code will still be used when the\n   certificates expire in 3 weeks.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D278888\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279900\n", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/2-qwac.binding", "build/pgo/certs/cert9.db", "build/pgo/certs/key4.db", "build/pgo/certs/mochitest.client", "netwerk/test/unit/client-cert.p12", "security/manager/ssl/tests/mochitest/browser/ca.pem", "security/manager/ssl/tests/mochitest/browser/client-cert-via-intermediate.pem", "securi