3ebcf749c", "953bccad04767aa5a61db8a8c4d34611317f77db"], "user": "ffxbld@lando.moz.tools"}, "24423": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2011114 - Make `EditorBase` stop dispatching `input` event immediately before or after `compositionend` in domains specified by prefs  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nWe're intentionally dispatching `input` events before and after\n`compositionend` for the compatibility with the spec and the other\nbrowsers which are based on WebKit (i.e., including Blink) and for\nthe backward compatibility and better behavior for web apps.\n\nThe hacky behavior works in the most web apps. However, we got a bug\nreport in bug 2006599. Therefore, we need to disable either `input`\nevent for specific website.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279488\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279976\n", "files": ["editor/libeditor/EditorBase.cpp", "editor/libeditor/EditorBase.h", "editor/libeditor/tests/mochitest.toml", "editor/libeditor/tests/test_selectable_input_event_dispatching_for_compositionend.html", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": "802e1799317693cbf5dd700d61d18d087fdcdebd", "git_parents": ["953bccad04767aa5a61db8a8c4d34611317f77db"], "node": "d19f18142285565ebd43cf7e30ed60495b4cf8ae", "parents": ["82b41cb3a75644a56e1b198578788e77a88bb977"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769088640, "git_changesets": ["802e1799317693cbf5dd700d61d18d087fdcdebd"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24424": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010986 - Make `nsWebBrowserFind::GetFrameSelection()` never return `Selection` for different document  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nPreviously, `nsIFrame::GetSelectionController()` returned `Selection`\nfor given `nsPresContext` if the frame is not a `TextControlFrame` [1].\nHowever, the `nsPresContext` may be for different window/document but\nit returned the non-related `Selection` and\n`nsWebBrowserFind::GetFrameSelection()` depend on the odd behavior [2].\n\nTherefore, the method needs to check whether the focused content is\nin the proper document or not.\n\n1. https://searchfox.org/firefox-main/rev/4852c962c4a137755524851aad30c772acd025bd/layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp#9201-9204\n2. https://searchfox.org/firefox-main/rev/4852c962c4a137755524851aad30c772acd025bd/toolkit/components/find/nsWebBrowserFind.cpp#666,671,691\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279606\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279975\n", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/selection/crashtests/find-with-moving-iframe.html", "toolkit/components/find/nsWebBrowserFind.cpp", "toolkit/components/find/nsWebBrowserFind.h"], "git_node": "a663af427bb4d3e5380b580c624d13f7b61798d5", "git_parents": ["802e1799317693cbf5dd700d61d18d087fdcdebd"], "node": "c73ea28596e42ebcfb22c5114a448926be01283f", "parents": ["d19f18142285565ebd43cf7e30ed60495b4cf8ae"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769088689, "git_changesets": ["a663af427bb4d3e5380b580c624d13f7b61798d5"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24425": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP remote-settings tld-suffixes ct-logs -  a=dmeehan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280037\n", "files": ["netwerk/dns/effective_tld_names.dat", "security/ct/CTKnownLogs.h", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "security/manager/tools/log_list.json", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons-bloomfilters.json", "services/settings/dumps/security-state/intermediates.json"], "git_node": "0b519e8060f5205064fe22ad8d946fbef1c26050", "git_parents": ["a663af427bb4d3e5380b580c624d13f7b61798d5"], "node": "2693160c4ea2d61368a198c8ff8dc1c2176162da", "parents": ["c73ea28596e42ebcfb