ion - missing PhenotypeContext when restoring contentUri tabs.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280296\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280444\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/support/ktx/src/main/java/mozilla/components/support/ktx/android/net/Uri.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/support/ktx/src/test/java/mozilla/components/support/ktx/android/net/UriTest.kt"], "git_node": "dcfa118b804fa005b2ce643054045dc44713b146", "git_parents": ["0e3021774d1dc0a7df7a7fd7afde24c920c67134"], "node": "865808a4313243abd1d7b2783e6c8cb502195bf8", "parents": ["3d9cb6902cbc5288622b0afead707fcf0f9b6719"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769520931, "git_changesets": ["dcfa118b804fa005b2ce643054045dc44713b146"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24474": {"changesets": [{"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2004898 - Skip the displayport clip on descendants of a sticky item built by the same frame as well.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D278932\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280539\n", "files": ["layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-in-checkerboard-land-2-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-in-checkerboard-land-2.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/reftest.list"], "git_node": "d8a3caf4961ec8f9af30944119fdbb79586eca38", "git_parents": ["dcfa118b804fa005b2ce643054045dc44713b146"], "node": "08b71c03c3c45f0478af4b5ea99cd50d09b47fd2", "parents": ["865808a4313243abd1d7b2783e6c8cb502195bf8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010481 - Do not write to StickyScrollContainer::mShouldFlatten if we're not painting to the window.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nThis value is only read if we're painting to the window.\n\nIf we write false to it during a hit test, with retained display lists\nthe next paint to the window can incorrectly use that value.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280348\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280540\n", "files": ["layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-retained-dl-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-retained-dl.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/reftest.list"], "git_node": "bb7e845518d6a0e76352f28096dcea12f09b529b", "git_parents": ["d8a3caf4961ec8f9af30944119fdbb79586eca38"], "node": "4d458a515c37e4d38aef1abe598ba617d0b38011", "parents": ["08b71c03c3c45f0478af4b5ea99cd50d09b47fd2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769521067, "git_changesets": ["d8a3caf4961ec8f9af30944119fdbb79586eca38", "bb7e845518d6a0e76352f28096dcea12f09b529b"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24475": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003capehrson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2011511 - Make VideoCaptureAndroid.java's startCapture and stopCapture idempotent.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D279869\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280583\n", "files": ["dom/media/systemservices/android_video_capture/java/src/org/webrtc/videoengine/VideoCaptureAndroid.java"], "git_node": "95849dd5590afe227e7957e78fcdea33df358ee2", "git_parents": ["bb7e845518d6a0e76352f28096dcea12f09b529b"], "node": "17c4b2c83c5d76374aaa915acbe82779a287cf9f", "parents": ["4d458a515c37e4d38aef1abe598ba617d0b38011"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769521304, "git_changesets": ["95849dd5590afe227e7957e78fcdea33df358ee2"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24476": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@lando.moz.tools\u003e", "branch": "tags-unified", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 699ed550566607b4287b45ea49b31511da5346f9 with FIREFOX_147_0_2_RELEASE a=tagging CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", 