94 - Show correct chatbot when switching from Blocked to a provider  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280808\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281018\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/config/aiFeatures.mjs", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_aiFeatures.js"], "git_node": "620f06a2d43f2dba66bccd990069e3812aa92580", "git_parents": ["fdc55dae0bd121aaaebdfaa4a0818298449d2208"], "node": "2df7ad2cc2dc287f9ba9b4007aefb5f2811e8b20", "parents": ["30d1590a22de38d0e429f4d9d8eb4a24230d33e4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2013061 - Hide empty AI Control rows when feature is hidden  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280810\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281019\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/config/aiFeatures.mjs"], "git_node": "e789d5a0e41c3f40b6375d9a24a443e1bbf62587", "git_parents": ["620f06a2d43f2dba66bccd990069e3812aa92580"], "node": "eda0e1c428b80aacd1a8e1053331bdc09bba9433", "parents": ["2df7ad2cc2dc287f9ba9b4007aefb5f2811e8b20"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769718020, "git_changesets": ["ffdaabb2822d545188164b138dadaa06f5cbfca3", "121673467b36e73c079217b8dd0aac7bf82b2076", "55ae6325503a75be5c5e769461666317219a1d73", "5574bbf850bf1e59e70f73c2f1f655f34f4ab5fb", "2437d0d4d8d60395a3c68f383a5b0d0d91540c02", "6565440f724cce0a5ef8e7c15f9569a001580f02", "645dece0c857500500f17a7a8d7868c9d6c3c899", "ca2241dd01509c8ce37f2946dd6789e7b91d88b8", "71d36b6ea04977a3d88f32f78fa43637694c33d2", "5b2122684a1dcc782656e45857c571b27be79c4a", "1bdf5fe4a9afabcdff2429952709ce871c747387", "67725e3a00969e8a745fbd30890ae4ee56baf704", "59279fbce2d61242ffce4059c25c8738db112967", "ebe4935a9b15aa28c3040dbb9e3a5e7f99427e4e", "2f06bb377e1b46a2e2be98d3f40102a725f3831e", "fdc55dae0bd121aaaebdfaa4a0818298449d2208", "620f06a2d43f2dba66bccd990069e3812aa92580", "e789d5a0e41c3f40b6375d9a24a443e1bbf62587"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24508": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1910011 - Update partitionKey before minting Client principal.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nThis patch addresses a partitionKey mismatch between a created Client\nprincipal and the intercepting ServiceWorker resulting from the case\nwhere an ABB iframe is created where the page load of the nested B is\nredirected back to be an ABA iframe.  The initial partition key for the\nB load lacks a foreign-bit, but the post-redirect A will (eventually)\nhave a foreign bit.\n\nCurrently, the partition key for cross-origin redirects is updated for\nCookieJarSettings by AntiTrackingUtils::UpdateAntiTrackingInfoForChannel\nin nsHttpChannel::AsyncOpen.  However, ClientChannelHelper samples the\nprincipal in its AsyncOnChannelRedirect listener which will happen\nstrictly before the AsyncOpen.  So it's essential for us to update the\ninfo before minting a partitioned principal for the channel in the CCH.\n\n(The InterceptedHttpChannel logic and redirect happens strictly after\nthe nsHttpChannel::AsyncOpen, which is how the ServiceWorker lookup\nis using a partitioned principal with the foreign bit set.)\n\nThis has been a longstanding problem since the introduction of the\nforeign bit that has been papered over by the logic in\nnsGlobalWindowInner::EnsureClientSource that checks if there is\nan existing mClientSource and then resets it silently if there is a\nmismatch in between the client principal and the foreign principal.\n(The initial mClientSource was from LoadInfo::TakeReservedClientSource\nand lacked a foreign bit in this case.)\n\nA related problem was solved in a similar way in bug 1736488 with\nhttps://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D211148 where we manually\ncalled the UpdateAntiTrackingInfoForChannel method before adding the\nClientChannelHelper in DocumentLoadListener.  This does raise the\nquestion of whether that call should be in ClientChannelHelper, but\nbug 1970169 since moved that call up and added dependent logic, so\nI think the answer is DocumentLoadListener remains the right place\nfor that call, but ClientChannelHelper probably is the right place\nfor this new call since responsibility for the client info is handed\noff from the DocumentLoadListener once it calls\nAddClientChannelHelperInParent.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280394\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280759\n", "files": ["dom/clients/manager/ClientChannelHelper.cpp", "toolkit/components/antitracking/test/browser/browser.toml", "toolkit/components/antitracking/test/browser/browser_partitionedABBredirectToABAServiceWorkers.js"], "git_node": "7164910e81811e88959eb5e23da36681f7c97ee3", "git_parents": ["e789d5a0e41c3f40b6375d9a24a443e1bbf62587"], "node": "6a6b9397cbc85ed3280ec1d14fe731d1e94c5f1c", "parents": ["eda0e1c428b80aacd1a8e1053331bdc09bba9433"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769721973, "git_changesets": ["7164910e81811e88959eb5e23da36681f7c97ee3"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24509": {"changesets": [{"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010958: [beta] Add logging and telemetry for location provider use  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nAdds indicators for calls to location providers.  Also makes logs easier to use.  The debug log includes too much that is not broadly useful.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280833\n", "files": ["dom/geolocation/metrics.yaml", "dom/system/NetworkGeolocationProvider.sys.mjs", "dom/system/android/AndroidLocationProvider.cpp", "dom/system/linux/GeoclueLocationProvider.cpp", "dom/system/linux/PortalLocationProvider.cpp", "dom/system/mac/CoreLocationLocationProvider.mm", "dom/system/windows/location/WindowsLocationChild.cpp", "testing/profiles/unittest-required/user.js"], "git_node": "120a0e4412aba908013c5e6e2c815ea64ffd9af3", "git_parents": ["7164910e81811e88959eb5e23da36681f7c97ee3"], "node": "89d58aba5505da3023756a0c4c6cc98b76cf2ced", "parents": ["6a6b9397cbc85ed3280ec1d14fe731d1e94c5f1c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010958: [beta] Cleanup some variable/function names in NetworkGeolocationProvider  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280834\n", "files": ["dom/system/NetworkGeolocationProvider.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "3ff37b3f0948f27a79317643a6546b8f85cdbaef", "git_parents": ["120a0e4412aba908013c5e6e2c815ea64ffd9af3"], "node": "32140324bedb61ff7a7de485e90ab0dc1985ad4f", "parents": ["89d58aba5505da3023756a0c4c6cc98b76cf2ced"], "tags": []}, {"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010958: [beta] Add telemetry for geolocation cache hits  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280835\n", "files": ["dom/geolocation/Geolocation.cpp", "dom/geolocation/metrics.yaml", "dom/system/NetworkGeolocationProvider.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "fa94b93de8d89e5f103972c88bae17a81e284787", "git_parents": ["3ff37b3f0948f27a79317643a6546b8f85cdbaef"], "node": "626dc0d1de6673dc1c9d18480b9012c88ffcc318", "parents": ["32140324bedb61ff7a7de485e90ab0dc1985ad4f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010958: [beta] Add logging to track MacOS geolocation permission  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nDetects things like loss of geolocation permission on MacOS.  We should be\nusing this info to update the Permissions Manager but, for now, this is just\nlogging.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280836\n", "files": ["dom/system/mac/CoreLocationLocationProvider.mm"], "git_node": "47734ad079a13f8d52c1cd9cdaf3bcdc8f88caca", "git_parents": ["fa94b93de8d89e5f103972c88bae17a81e284787"], "node": "4193f6932b5853b63f6d3ef0847634dc5650046b", "parents": ["626dc0d1de6673dc1c9d18480b9012c88ffcc318"], "tags": []}, {"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010958: [beta] Add telemetry for system geolocation failures  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nRecords when we fail to get location and why.  The most important distinction\nis between permission denial and other errors, but we also collect raw error\ncodes, in case of surprises.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280837\n", "files": ["dom/geolocation/metrics.yaml", "dom/system/linux/GeoclueLocationProvider.cpp", "dom/system/linux/PortalLocationProvider.cpp", "dom/system/mac/CoreLocationLocationProvider.mm", "dom/system/windows/location/WindowsLocationChild.cpp"], "git_node": "17e11468ddb634e3ec4f74853fc068857851484f", "git_parents": ["47734ad079a13f8d52c1cd9cdaf3bcdc8f88caca"], "node": "d93ffb4b032e986ed0c3c7cb3d2aed7d64fceb86", "parents": ["4193f6932b5853b63f6d3ef0847634dc5650046b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "unknown \u003cdaparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2010958: [beta] Add tests for new geolocation telemetry  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nAdded checks for system and network request count telemetry to existing tests.\nAlso fixes an issue with a test presenting a user prompt (which causes it to\ntimeout), and some minor bugs.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280838\n", "files": ["dom/geolocation/test/mochitest/test_native_provider.html", "dom/geolocation/test/unit/test_geolocation_provider.js", "dom/geolocation/test/unit/test_geolocation_provider_timeout.js"], "git_node": "ee8cf2b6f2d110089acffbab3a0c4741a2046e3c", "git_parents": ["17e11468ddb634e3ec4f74853fc068857851484f"], "node": "1042b20ddf8a2f4d33dfd25029d4ef0a585cffb4", "parents": ["d93ffb4b032e986ed0c3c7cb3d2aed7d64fceb86"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769722849, "git_changesets": ["120a0e4412aba908013c5e6e2c815ea64ffd9af3", "3ff37b3f0948f27a79317643a6546b8f85cdbaef", "fa94b93de8d89e5f103972c88bae17a81e284787", "47734ad079a13f8d52c1cd9cdaf3bcdc8f88caca", "17e11468ddb634e3ec4f74853fc068857851484f", "ee8cf2b6f2d110089acffbab3a0c4741a2046e3c"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24510": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2013402 - Fix stylelint rule name in block-ai-confirmation-dialog.css  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281086\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/config/block-ai-confirmation-dialog.css"], "git_node": "0dbd6a5be50e7925c9745734efe0cd178461c25f", "git_parents": ["ee8cf2b6f2d110089acffbab3a0c4741a2046e3c"], "node": "def570e3753fdd5df2e0e48aabf823b4a2bf8605", "parents": ["1042b20ddf8a2f4d33dfd25029d4ef0a585cffb4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1769725698, "git_changesets": ["0dbd6a5be50e7925c9745734efe0cd178461c25f"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24511": {"changesets": [{"author": "Calixte Denizet \u003ccalixte.denizet@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2012691 - Make the 'Available' entry usable in the dropdown for pdf.js in the AI settings  a=dmeehan\n\nAIFeatures.reset resets the prefs to their default value.\nSo this patch just sets pdfjs.enableAltTextModelDownload and pdfjs.enableGuessAltText to false in order to make the feature disabled but available.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280667\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281056\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/pdfjs/PdfJsOverridePrefs.js", "toolkit/components/pdfjs/test/browser_pdfjs_aifeature_settings.js", "toolkit/components/pdfjs/test/browser_pdfjs_alttext_load_engine.js", "toolkit/components/pdfjs/test/browser_pdfjs_alttext_telemetry.js", "toolkit/components/pdfjs/test/browser_pdfjs_alttext_two_tabs.js", "toolkit/components/pdfjs/test/browser_pdfjs_update_preferences.js"], "git_node"