roblems:\n\n1. Previously, we explicitly never set mIsEndOfLineInsertionPoint to true at the start of a paragraph. This is exactly the case we're dealing with here and that behaviour is incorrect. Instead, we now have a much narrower check for the specific exception we're trying to detect: the start of the editor.\n2. GetCaretRect vertically aligns the rect to the top of the line. To do this, it relies on mIsEndOfLineInsertionPoint being set correctly, which it wasn't previously. Thus, GetCaretRect was using the first character on the next line, resulting in a rect with negative height.\n3. UIA calls TextLeafRange::LineRects, which clips the bounds to the content area. Since the caret rect previously had negative height, it was clipped completely and removed. Thus, UIA previously returned no bounds at all.\n\nAll of this is fixed by correctly setting mIsEndOfLineInsertionPoint in this case.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281126\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282508\n", "files": ["accessible/base/TextLeafRange.cpp", "accessible/tests/browser/bounds/browser_caret_rect.js", "accessible/tests/browser/text/browser_text_caret.js"], "git_node": "6146da9f747474737628a11353cbbc4a78275965", "git_parents": ["79ea05aa5e84b6960951a53003ebff8635211e12"], "node": "b9eb1e938b22a0b712e4a6ab7cb59019321c4485", "parents": ["cf0b5ac848653eaaeef8951b81136b2bdb9db5be"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770717083, "git_changesets": ["6146da9f747474737628a11353cbbc4a78275965"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24651": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Seward \u003cjseward@acm.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2013616. r=rhunt a=dmeehan. DONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282335\n", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmGcObject.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmInstance.cpp"], "git_node": "99a51e7c78a6598da941017b62f807d56c32f8d9", "git_parents": ["6146da9f747474737628a11353cbbc4a78275965"], "node": "fb2521c9f56f15017b6c1fcfc246a20664895536", "parents": ["b9eb1e938b22a0b712e4a6ab7cb59019321c4485"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770717126, "git_changesets": ["99a51e7c78a6598da941017b62f807d56c32f8d9"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24652": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ben Visness \u003cbvisness@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2013741: Clean up misleading comments in array.fill.  a=dmeehan\n\nThe comments were pulled from a different array method and were slightly\nmisleading about how the assembly was generated.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281627\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282430\n", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmBaselineCompile.cpp"], "git_node": "badafa0ba4e7d61f96291308f97dfb498bc07dee", "git_parents": ["99a51e7c78a6598da941017b62f807d56c32f8d9"], "node": "3fcc45a60e12e107da14894f63e01070a61cca69", "parents": ["fb2521c9f56f15017b6c1fcfc246a20664895536"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770717275, "git_changesets": ["badafa0ba4e7d61f96291308f97dfb498bc07dee"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24653": {"changesets": [{"author": "Frederik Braun \u003cfbraun@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2012331 - ensure consistent MediaKeys lifetime  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280379\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282592\n", "files": ["dom/media/eme/MediaKeys.cpp"], "git_node": "c58b190a1016222991b74a0b6a9ed575ce4547a7", "git_parents": ["badafa0ba4e7d61f96291308f97dfb498bc07dee"], "node": "0eac8240ae47a1e1f3d3bb18c36b51411f66d146", "parents": ["3fcc45a60e12e107da14894f63e01070a61cca69"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770730259, "git_changesets": ["c58b190a1016222991b74a0b6a9ed575ce4547a7"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24654": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Schuster \u003ctschuster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2012984 - Use the ClientInfo for fetch with keepalive.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D280924\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282584\n", "files": ["dom/fetch/FetchParent.cpp", "dom/fetch/FetchService.cpp", "dom/fetch/FetchService.h"], "git_node": "8622adb072f01cffe4fc79da25967ce7097426f6", "git_parents": ["c58b190a1016222991b74a0b6a9ed575ce4547a7"], "node": "a57a0fdba503d73ec08752e2ce7db23b9d344c7f", "parents": ["0eac8240ae47a1e1f3d3bb18c36b51411f66d146"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770730301, "git_changesets": ["8622adb072f01cffe4fc79da25967ce7097426f6"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24655": {"changesets": [{"author": "Greg Stoll \u003cgreg@gregstoll.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015266  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282425\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282516\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/other/CombinedStacks.cpp"], "git_node": "33a1525446dc7dc4361fde7872cbf4ac0434f9d0", "git_parents": ["8622adb072f01cffe4fc79da25967ce7097426f6"], "node": "dc5854c871aa1f26213808fa97fe7004c79791f1", "parents": ["a57a0fdba503d73ec08752e2ce7db23b9d344c7f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770734453, "git_changesets": ["33a1525446dc7dc4361fde7872cbf4ac0434f9d0"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24656": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dave Townsend \u003cdtownsend@oxymoronical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2014616: Always create the Profile Groups folder in case it is missing.  a=dmeehan\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282027\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282606\n", "files": ["browser/components/profiles/tests/unit/test_fail_recover_storeID.js", "toolkit/profile/ProfilesDatastoreService.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "6069ea49daa8d864cc878babe6127bdb986897fd", "git_parents": ["33a1525446dc7dc4361fde7872cbf4ac0434f9d0"], "node": "208079f4b7bd9173691b74484939d38f09ea9748", "parents": ["dc5854c871aa1f26213808fa97fe7004c79791f1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770734875, "git_changesets": ["6069ea49daa8d864cc878babe6127bdb986897fd"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24657": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015179. In image SourceBuffer, don't set the capacity of a chunk to zero, just remove the chunk.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nThe SourceBuffer::Compact change is the fix for this bug. The other changes are things I noticed or pro-active defensive fixes.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282263\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282574\n", "files": ["image/SourceBuffer.cpp", "image/SourceBuffer.h"], "git_node": "67a3bfc455008dfd8d2d023cac2097100a83e166", "git_parents": ["6069ea49daa8d864cc878babe6127bdb986897fd"], "node": "a0100a38d13008b44055b79bb6d444042825ec6e", "parents": ["208079f4b7bd9173691b74484939d38f09ea9748"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770747054, "git_changesets": ["67a3bfc455008dfd8d2d023cac2097100a83e166"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24658": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2013561 - Mark symbols referenced by uncollected zones as part of weak marking  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nThe current issue is that we only do this when a weakmap's color changes. This\nmight only happen once at a time when the current mark color is not the one we\nneed to mark the symbol, resulting in the symbol not getting marked.\n\nInstead scan atoms zone ephemeron edge sources as part of weak marking since\nthis happens per color.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281765\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282670\n", "files": ["js/src/gc/GCRuntime.h", "js/src/gc/Marking.cpp", "js/src/gc/Sweeping.cpp", "js/src/gc/WeakMap-inl.h"], "git_node": "22cfeede6d8b6a3d2512fd99ec212179afed2524", "git_parents": ["67a3bfc455008dfd8d2d023cac2097100a83e166"], "node": "1b33abdbdfa40146c9f54fd485531660624b9365", "parents": ["a0100a38d13008b44055b79bb6d444042825ec6e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770747097, "git_changesets": ["22cfeede6d8b6a3d2512fd99ec212179afed2524"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24659": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2013549 - Give synthetic module environments a *namespace* property the same as for cyclic modules  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nModule environments are given this special internal property that can hold a\nreference to the module's namespace object if needed. The property itself is\nused when module's namespace is imported and then that binding is exported. An\nimport of that uses the binding of the module namespace object in the original\nobject's environment.\n\nFor cyclic modules this happens by Parser::moduleBody adding a fake declaration\nfor this name, but this is not done for synthetic modules which don't come from\nparsed JS. The patch adds this name for synthetic modules.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D281434\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282668\n", "files": ["js/src/builtin/ModuleObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/EnvironmentObject.h", "js/src/vm/Modules.cpp", "js/src/vm/Scope.cpp"], "git_node": "8292fe28a961aaa1ec09c029afa65b9ec89ae353", "git_parents": ["22cfeede6d8b6a3d2512fd99ec212179afed2524"], "node": "c79db4af040e584d423a59cec3246404916d4112", "parents": ["1b33abdbdfa40146c9f54fd485531660624b9365"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770747140, "git_changesets": ["8292fe28a961aaa1ec09c029afa65b9ec89ae353"], "user": "dmeehan@mozilla.com"}, "24660": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2014001 - Skip first unaligned filter. r=tnikkel a=dmeehan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282323\n