, "parents": ["9a24223f383fe15618b2e145ca4c7dfa94c06210"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770800747, "git_changesets": ["6aa4e1ddaffaf29f693ea6c82ee6e95600913a5d", "86202406a4b9eb19303db42ad7d6a00103213b0f"], "user": "ffxbld@lando.moz.tools"}, "24663": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015488 - Support backdrop on outer \u003csvg\u003e / \u003ciframe\u003e / \u003cimg\u003e.  a=dmeehan DONTBUILD\n\nAdd exceptions for a few elements that do rely on their frame tree\nsize (mostly text controls). These are fixable but separate bug at the\nvery least.\n\nAdd reftests for \u003ciframe\u003e and \u003cimg\u003e. Also, test all HTML elements in all\nwriting modes to ensure that they don't trigger assertions.\n\nThe \u003csvg\u003e case can't be easily reftested, afaict, because fullscreen\nwill change the size of the reftest window and \u003csvg\u003e doesn't support\npopover.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282451\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D282702\n", "files": ["layout/base/nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp", "layout/generic/FrameClasses.py", "layout/generic/nsIFrame.h", "layout/generic/nsImageFrame.cpp", "layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp", "layout/svg/SVGUtils.cpp", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/popovers/popover-attribute-all-elements.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/popovers/popover-iframe-backdrop.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/popovers/popover-img-backdrop-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/html/semantics/popovers/popover-img-backdrop.html"], "git_node": "9c15f947ca7ad1e603b1741857a85f1a5aa6749f", "git_parents": ["86202406a4b9eb19303db42ad7d6a00103213b0f"], "node": "22e896b56d5ffcaadaa43e5060605787777cf21c", "parents": ["114ae4241ed161abd1be421e48e899725c3c3e16"], "tags": []}], "date": 1770801180, "git_changesets": ["9c15f947ca7ad1e603b1741857a85f1a5aa6749f"], "user": "dmeehan